025/**
026 * Allows the definition of input and output data types.
027 *
028 * <p>
029 * The Schema Object allows the definition of input and output data types for Swagger 2.0, including objects,
030 * primitives, and arrays. This object is an extended subset of the JSON Schema Specification Draft 4, with
031 * additional extensions provided by the Swagger Specification to allow for more complete documentation.
032 *
033 * <h5 class='section'>Swagger Specification:</h5>
034 * <p>
035 * The Schema Object supports all properties from JSON Schema Draft 4, including but not limited to:
036 * <ul class='spaced-list'>
037 *    <li><c>type</c> (string) - The data type. Values: <js>"string"</js>, <js>"number"</js>, <js>"integer"</js>, <js>"boolean"</js>, <js>"array"</js>, <js>"object"</js>, <js>"file"</js>
038 *    <li><c>format</c> (string) - The format modifier (e.g., <js>"int32"</js>, <js>"int64"</js>, <js>"float"</js>, <js>"double"</js>, <js>"date"</js>, <js>"date-time"</js>)
039 *    <li><c>title</c> (string) - A short title for the schema
040 *    <li><c>description</c> (string) - A description of the schema
041 *    <li><c>default</c> (any) - The default value
042 *    <li><c>multipleOf</c> (number) - Must be a multiple of this value
043 *    <li><c>maximum</c> (number) - Maximum value (inclusive by default)
044 *    <li><c>exclusiveMaximum</c> (boolean) - If true, maximum is exclusive
045 *    <li><c>minimum</c> (number) - Minimum value (inclusive by default)
046 *    <li><c>exclusiveMinimum</c> (boolean) - If true, minimum is exclusive
047 *    <li><c>maxLength</c> (integer) - Maximum string length
048 *    <li><c>minLength</c> (integer) - Minimum string length
049 *    <li><c>pattern</c> (string) - Regular expression pattern the string must match
050 *    <li><c>maxItems</c> (integer) - Maximum array length
051 *    <li><c>minItems</c> (integer) - Minimum array length
052 *    <li><c>uniqueItems</c> (boolean) - If true, array items must be unique
053 *    <li><c>maxProperties</c> (integer) - Maximum number of object properties
054 *    <li><c>minProperties</c> (integer) - Minimum number of object properties
055 *    <li><c>required</c> (array of string) - Required property names
056 *    <li><c>enum</c> (array) - Possible values for this schema
057 *    <li><c>properties</c> (map of {@link SchemaInfo}) - Object property definitions
058 *    <li><c>items</c> ({@link Items}) - Schema for array items
059 *    <li><c>allOf</c> (array of {@link SchemaInfo}) - Must validate against all schemas
060 *    <li><c>discriminator</c> (string) - Property name for polymorphism (Swagger extension)
061 *    <li><c>readOnly</c> (boolean) - Relevant only for Schema properties (Swagger extension)
062 *    <li><c>xml</c> ({@link Xml}) - XML representation details (Swagger extension)
063 *    <li><c>externalDocs</c> ({@link ExternalDocumentation}) - Additional external documentation (Swagger extension)
064 *    <li><c>example</c> (any) - Example value (Swagger extension)
065 * </ul>
066 *
067 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
068 * <p class='bjava'>
069 *    <jc>// Construct using SwaggerBuilder.</jc>
070 *    SchemaInfo <jv>info</jv> = <jsm>schemaInfo</jsm>()
071 *       .type(<js>"string"</js>)
072 *       .title(<js>"foo"</js>)
073 *
074 *    <jc>// Serialize using JsonSerializer.</jc>
075 *    String <jv>json</jv> = Json.<jsm>from</jsm>(<jv>info</jv>);
076 *
077 *    <jc>// Or just use toString() which does the same as above.</jc>
078 *    <jv>json</jv> = <jv>info</jv>.toString();
079 * </p>
080 * <p class='bjson'>
081 *    <jc>// Output</jc>
082 *    {
083 *       <js>"type"</js>: <js>"string"</js>,
084 *       <js>"title"</js>: <js>"foo"</js>
085 *    }
086 * </p>
087 *
088 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
089 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2/#schema-object">Swagger 2.0 Specification &gt; Schema Object</a>
090 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/docs/specification/2-0/data-models/">Swagger Data Models</a>
091 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://json-schema.org/">JSON Schema Specification</a>
092 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanSwagger2">juneau-bean-swagger-v2</a>
093 * </ul>
094 */
095@FluentSetters
096public class SchemaInfo extends SwaggerElement {
097
098   private String
099      format,
100      title,
101      description,
102      pattern,
103      type,
104      discriminator,
105      ref;
106   private Number
107      multipleOf,
108      maximum,
109      minimum;
110   private Integer
111      maxLength,
112      minLength,
113      maxItems,
114      minItems,
115      maxProperties,
116      minProperties;
117   private Boolean
118      exclusiveMaximum,
119      exclusiveMinimum,
120      uniqueItems,
121      readOnly,
122      required;
123   private Object
124      _default,  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.
125      example;
126   private Items items;
127   private Xml xml;
128   private ExternalDocumentation externalDocs;
129   private Set<Object> _enum;  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.
130   private Set<SchemaInfo> allOf;
131   private Set<String>
132      requiredProperties;
133   private Map<String,SchemaInfo> properties;
134   private SchemaInfo additionalProperties;
135
136   /**
137    * Default constructor.
138    */
139   public SchemaInfo() {}
140
141   /**
142    * Copy constructor.
143    *
144    * @param copyFrom The object to copy.
145    */
146   public SchemaInfo(SchemaInfo copyFrom) {
147      super(copyFrom);
148
149      this.additionalProperties = copyFrom.additionalProperties == null ? null : copyFrom.additionalProperties.copy();
150      this.allOf = copyOf(copyFrom.allOf);
151      this._default = copyFrom._default;
152      this.description = copyFrom.description;
153      this.discriminator = copyFrom.discriminator;
154      this._enum = copyOf(copyFrom._enum);
155      this.example = copyFrom.example;
156      this.exclusiveMaximum = copyFrom.exclusiveMaximum;
157      this.exclusiveMinimum = copyFrom.exclusiveMinimum;
158      this.externalDocs = copyFrom.externalDocs == null ? null : copyFrom.externalDocs.copy();
159      this.format = copyFrom.format;
160      this.items = copyFrom.items == null ? null : copyFrom.items.copy();
161      this.maximum = copyFrom.maximum;
162      this.maxItems = copyFrom.maxItems;
163      this.maxLength = copyFrom.maxLength;
164      this.maxProperties = copyFrom.maxProperties;
165      this.minimum = copyFrom.minimum;
166      this.minItems = copyFrom.minItems;
167      this.minLength = copyFrom.minLength;
168      this.minProperties = copyFrom.minProperties;
169      this.multipleOf = copyFrom.multipleOf;
170      this.pattern = copyFrom.pattern;
171      this.readOnly = copyFrom.readOnly;
172      this.ref = copyFrom.ref;
173      this.required = copyFrom.required;
174      this.requiredProperties = copyOf(copyFrom.requiredProperties);
175      this.title = copyFrom.title;
176      this.type = copyFrom.type;
177      this.uniqueItems = copyFrom.uniqueItems;
178      this.xml = copyFrom.xml == null ? null : copyFrom.xml.copy();
179      this.properties = copyOf(copyFrom.properties, SchemaInfo::copy);
180   }
181
182   /**
183    * Make a deep copy of this object.
184    *
185    * @return A deep copy of this object.
186    */
187   public SchemaInfo copy() {
188      return new SchemaInfo(this);
189   }

1188   /**
1189    * Resolves any <js>"$ref"</js> attributes in this element.
1190    *
1191    * @param swagger The swagger document containing the definitions.
1192    * @param refStack Keeps track of previously-visited references so that we don't cause recursive loops.
1193    * @param maxDepth
1194    *    The maximum depth to resolve references.
1195    *    <br>After that level is reached, <c>$ref</c> references will be left alone.
1196    *    <br>Useful if you have very complex models and you don't want your swagger page to be overly-complex.
1197    * @return
1198    *    This object with references resolved.
1199    *    <br>May or may not be the same object.
1200    */
1201   public SchemaInfo resolveRefs(Swagger swagger, Deque<String> refStack, int maxDepth) {
1202
1203      if (ref != null) {
1204         if (refStack.contains(ref) || refStack.size() >= maxDepth)
1205            return this;
1206         refStack.addLast(ref);
1207         var r = swagger.findRef(ref, SchemaInfo.class).resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1208         refStack.removeLast();
1209         return r;
1210      }
1211
1212      if (items != null)
1213         items = items.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1214
1215      if (properties != null)
1216         properties.entrySet().forEach(x -> x.setValue(x.getValue().resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth)));
1217
1218      if (additionalProperties != null)
1219         additionalProperties = additionalProperties.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1220
1221      this.example = null;
1222
1223      return this;
1224   }
